  <div class="sg-section-label">09 — Motion</div>
  <h2 class="sg-section-title">MOTION & ANIMATION</h2>
  <p class="sg-section-desc">Motion in Mateo should feel natural and purposeful — like a gentle breeze, not a storm. Every animation either directs attention, provides feedback, or eases a spatial transition.</p>

  <div class="sg-subsection">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">Easing Curves</div>
    <div class="sg-motion-item">
      <div class="sg-motion-dot"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="sg-motion-name">Standard</div>
        <div class="sg-motion-spec">cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1.0)</div>
        <div class="sg-motion-use">Default for most transitions — buttons, cards, hover states</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-motion-item">
      <div class="sg-motion-dot" style="background: var(--palm-600);"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="sg-motion-name">Enter</div>
        <div class="sg-motion-spec">cubic-bezier(0.0, 0.0, 0.2, 1.0)</div>
        <div class="sg-motion-use">Elements entering the viewport — modals, sheets, toasts</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-motion-item">
      <div class="sg-motion-dot" style="background: var(--drift-600);"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="sg-motion-name">Exit</div>
        <div class="sg-motion-spec">cubic-bezier(0.4, 0.0, 1.0, 1.0)</div>
        <div class="sg-motion-use">Elements leaving — dismissals, deletions, closes</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-subsection">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">Duration Scale</div>
    <table class="sg-table" style="max-width: 480px;">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Token</th><th>Duration</th><th>Use</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>duration-fast</td><td>100ms</td><td>Opacity, color shifts</td></tr>
        <tr><td>duration-normal</td><td>200ms</td><td>Hover, focus, small transitions</td></tr>
        <tr><td>duration-slow</td><td>300ms</td><td>Expand/collapse, slide-ins</td></tr>
        <tr><td>duration-deliberate</td><td>450ms</td><td>Full-screen transitions, page shifts</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-warn" style="max-width: 560px;">Always respect <code class="sg-code" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">prefers-reduced-motion</code>. When the OS-level setting is active, collapse all transitions to instant (0ms) or reduce to a single subtle opacity fade.</div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     14. ACCESSIBILITY
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="sg-section" id="accessibility">
  <div class="sg-section-label">10 — Accessibility</div>
  <h2 class="sg-section-title">ACCESSIBILITY</h2>
  <p class="sg-section-desc">Mateo targets WCAG 2.1 AA compliance across all platforms. Accessibility is a baseline requirement, not a feature — every component and pattern in this system is designed to meet these standards.</p>

  <div class="sg-subsection">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">Color Contrast</div>
    <table class="sg-table" style="max-width: 600px;">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Combination</th><th>Ratio</th><th>Passes</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>neutral-900 on white</td><td>15.4:1</td><td>AAA ✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td>lagoon-600 on white</td><td>4.8:1</td><td>AA (large text) ✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td>White on lagoon-600</td><td>4.8:1</td><td>AA (large text) ✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td>lagoon-800 on white</td><td>8.2:1</td><td>AAA ✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td>White on lagoon-700</td><td>5.9:1</td><td>AA ✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td>neutral-700 on white</td><td>5.6:1</td><td>AA ✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td>drift-800 on drift-100</td><td>5.1:1</td><td>AA ✓</td></tr>
        <tr><td>palm-800 on palm-100</td><td>5.4:1</td><td>AA ✓</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="sg-note" style="max-width: 560px;">For body text at 15px, always use neutral-700 or darker against white/light backgrounds to meet AA for normal text (4.5:1 minimum). Lagoon-600 on white (4.8:1) is acceptable for large text only (18px+ regular or 14px+ bold).</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-subsection">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">Touch & Click Targets</div>
    <table class="sg-table" style="max-width: 440px;">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Platform</th><th>Minimum Size</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>iOS</td><td>44 × 44pt</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Android</td><td>48 × 48dp</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Web</td><td>44 × 44px (preferred)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-subsection">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">Focus Management</div>
    <p class="sg-subsection-desc">All interactive elements must show a visible focus indicator for keyboard navigation. The standard focus ring is a 3px box-shadow using lagoon-100 with a lagoon-600 border, matching the input focus style. Never use <code class="sg-code">outline: none</code> without providing an alternative visible indicator.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-subsection">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">Screen Reader Considerations</div>
    <p class="sg-subsection-desc">Images must have descriptive alt text (destination photos should describe the scene, not just the location name). Decorative icons use <code class="sg-code">aria-hidden="true"</code>. Navigation landmarks must be clearly defined. Rating information must be announced in context, not as disconnected numbers.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     15. VOICE & TONE
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="sg-section sg-section--warm" id="voice">
  <div class="sg-section-label">11 — Language</div>
  <h2 class="sg-section-title">VOICE & TONE</h2>
  <p class="sg-section-desc">Mateo speaks like a well-traveled friend — warm, knowledgeable, and genuinely helpful. Not a tour guide reading from a script, and never a pushy salesperson.</p>

  <div class="sg-grid-2" style="max-width: 640px;">
    <div class="sg-principle" style="border-color: var(--lagoon-600);">
      <div class="sg-principle-title">WE ARE</div>
      <p class="sg-principle-body">Encouraging, specific, conversational, culturally respectful. "You'll want to visit the night market — the grilled skewers are worth the wait."</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-principle" style="border-color: var(--error);">
      <div class="sg-principle-title">WE ARE NOT</div>
      <p class="sg-principle-body">Generic, hyperbolic, pressuring, jargon-heavy. "Unlock amazing experiences in this stunning paradise! Book now before it's too late!"</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-subsection" style="margin-top: 32px;">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">UI Copy Guidelines</div>
    <div class="sg-do-dont" style="max-width: 640px;">
      <div class="sg-do">
        <div class="sg-do-label">Do</div>
        <div class="sg-do-text">
          Use sentence case for all UI text.<br>
          "Save trip" not "Save Trip".<br><br>
          Be specific about actions: "Add to saved trips" tells the user exactly what happens.<br><br>
          Empty states invite action: "You haven't saved any trips yet. Start exploring?"
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sg-dont">
        <div class="sg-dont-label">Don't</div>
        <div class="sg-dont-text">
          Use Title Case In Navigation Or Buttons.<br><br>
          Be vague: "Submit" says nothing. "Processing…" says nothing.<br><br>
          Apologize in error states: "Oops! Something went wrong!" — instead: "Couldn't load trips. Check your connection and try again."
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     16. PLATFORM NOTES
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="sg-section" id="platform">
  <div class="sg-section-label">12 — Platform</div>
  <h2 class="sg-section-title">PLATFORM-SPECIFIC NOTES</h2>
  <p class="sg-section-desc">Mateo should feel native on each platform while remaining unmistakably Mateo. Adapt the system to each platform's conventions without losing brand identity.</p>

  <div class="sg-grid-3">
    <div class="sg-principle" style="border-color: var(--lagoon-600);">
      <div class="sg-principle-title">WEB</div>
      <p class="sg-principle-body">
        Top navigation bar with Bebas Neue wordmark. Hover states on all interactive elements. Content max-width 1200px. Cards display in 2–4 column grids depending on viewport. Use CSS custom properties (the tokens defined in this guide) as the single source of truth.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-principle" style="border-color: var(--neutral-500);">
      <div class="sg-principle-title">iOS</div>
      <p class="sg-principle-body">
        Bottom tab bar (UITabBarController). Use SF Symbols alongside Lucide where system icons are expected (share, back, settings). Respect safe areas. Use system haptics for save/delete confirmations. Navigation follows UINavigationController push/pop pattern.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-principle" style="border-color: var(--palm-600);">
      <div class="sg-principle-title">ANDROID</div>
      <p class="sg-principle-body">
        Bottom navigation with Material 3 component. 48dp minimum touch targets. Edge-to-edge rendering with system bar tinting (lagoon-700 for status bar). Use Material motion patterns for shared-element transitions between card and detail views.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-subsection" style="margin-top: 32px;">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">What Stays Consistent Across Platforms</div>
    <table class="sg-table" style="max-width: 600px;">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Element</th><th>Rule</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Color palette</td><td>Identical hex values everywhere</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Bebas Neue</td><td>Same usage (headlines, buttons, ratings) across all platforms</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Nunito</td><td>Body font on all platforms (not replaced by system fonts)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Avatar / logo</td><td>Same asset, same clear space rules</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Card structure</td><td>Same visual hierarchy (photo → title → subtitle → rating)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Spacing tokens</td><td>Same scale, adapted to platform density</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="sg-subsection">
    <div class="sg-subsection-title">What Adapts Per Platform</div>
    <table class="sg-table" style="max-width: 600px;">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Element</th><th>Web</th><th>iOS</th><th>Android</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Primary nav</td><td>Top bar</td><td>Bottom tabs</td><td>Bottom nav</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Back navigation</td><td>Breadcrumbs</td><td>Swipe / ‹ Back</td><td>← arrow</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Modals</td><td>Center dialog</td><td>Bottom sheet</td><td>Bottom sheet</td></tr>
        <tr><td>System icons</td><td>Lucide</td><td>Lucide + SF Symbols</td><td>Lucide</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Touch targets</td><td>44px</td><td>44pt</td><td>48dp</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

